THOUSANDS of people from across the city gathered in the West End to begin the summer festivities at the Gibson Street Gala.The day brought together a variety of people from the community from local people, traders, churches and schools.Children enjoyed the free activities and lined up at the face painting stall.Chairperson of the organising committee and local Councillor Martin McElroy said: &quot;The day went really well considering the horrible weather.&quot;I think everyone was having fun and the stalls were a great success.&quot;This weekend saw the beginning of a number of high profile events in the West End of the city, including the Mela and West End Festival Parade.